<br>
Dear Grey Council,<br>
<br>
At Mucho's prompting, and due to the fact that I can't stay on much longer, I'm posting here about the events of the past 24 hours.<br>
<br>
I received a call late last night from my best friend, Ed. Ed, in case folks didn't know, was Tawm/Soulspurn. He sounded down, but I was at work and couldn't do anything. But, when I went to his house this morning, his room-mate told me he'd hung himself sometime around 4 am.<br>
<br>
He left a letter for me, and told me to take over the account, tell the people on /friends what happened, and to have fun. I don't know if I will use it at all, and I don't know if you folks want to remove me or what. I have very very little experience with EQ, and what I do know I learned from watching Ed.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry to be the bearer of bad news, I know he told me when he rejoined you folks it was a really happy moment for him. Let me know what you want to do, and I'll check back again.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
Jacob <br>
Soulspurn Dethcaller Warlock of Grey Council<br>
Tawm Windsong Semi-Retired Maestro of Grey Council<br>
<br>
End of paste.<br>
<br>
<br>
I have no idea why Ed would do such a thing, but I wanted the Xev community to be aware of this loss.<br>
