<br>
The moment I read the post from this &quot;friend,&quot; warning sirens went up. After 23 years online, I've seen it all -- including this. And more than once. So I started investigating it. I expressed my concerns to the officers. I tracked down Tawm's actual address and phone number fairly easily (note to those who do online hoaxes -- make yourself invisible first). <br>
<br>
The address led me to a small town in California in the Santa Barbara area. No police or fire department in this town, but of course the Californial Highway Patrol has an outpost there. I called them with my information. Ten minutes later, I was told that any suicides would go through the coronor's office. Nothing like this was reported. Not in that county, not in nearby counties.<br>
<br>
I then confronted this person in email. I asked for information on funeral arrangements, etc. Things that a best friend would know. I got even more warning bells. I knew, at this point, it was a hoax. <br>
<br>
Tonight I found this person online on an alt. It took nearly an hour, and I heard a bunch of lies first. Eventually, he folded and admitted the hoax. There is no friend. This was done by Tawm/Soulspurn himself. I have asked for an apology on our General boards. I have asked VI to remove his account, although I doubt that will be done. I asked for that not to punish Tawm but to protect those in other guilds, on other servers, from someone who is very unstable and needs help. <br>
<br>
I've posted all of this to make it clear this was a hoax. It's so unbelievable. On behalf of GC, I'm both embarrassed and sad.<br>
<br>
This is a crushing blow to us. We didn't ask for this sort of drama junkie stuff. We just want to have some structure in which to group together, do the things we can in game, etc. We looked with hope to the next expansion as a boon for small, more casual guilds. <br>
<br>
We're a small guild now. We don't attract power players. We have a core group of daily players but mostly a lot of more casual players. After everything that has happened with GC, we asked ourselves what we wanted out of this game. What we wanted was a small corner of Xev to just hang out together, at least for now, and then to rebuild very, very slowly. We are tremendously picky about who joins. Not because we're uber or elite. Because we want folks to really understand that the friendships we develop in game are paramount, that anything else is secondary. This isn't to say at all that you can't have guilds of friends that also do all the amazing stuff in the game. Not at all. It's to say where we are right now. All we want to do is log on as we can, have some fun, get to know each other, and have some harmony together as we do it.<br>
<br>
Tonight I really hurt for all of those in GC, because we were put through a sort of torment that no one should go through. I'm glad, but not happy, that I was able to track down the truth. I feel very sorry for Tawm/Soulspurn who is obviously in need of help. <br>
<br>
I've never been so sorry to be right from the beginning, either.  <p> <font face="Arial"><div align="center"><font color="Red"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359805" target="_blank">Epix</a></a><br>Arcanist<br>Guild Leader, Grey Council on Xev<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=epix2000>Epix2000</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/30/03 12:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daniell1>daniell1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://canflag.ptbcanadian.com/images/buttons/iamv2.wpcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Town Idiot</span><br>  Posts: 399<br> <font color=#330000>(7/30/03 7:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loss of a guildie and friend</span><hr size=1> This is a common thing to happen on the internet.  Person A is unhappy that he/she is not getting attention.  Claims to be person B's &quot;Best Friend&quot; and that person A killed himself.  Then sees an outpouring of support and love.  <br>
